Simple Substitution Cipher:

A basic Python script that encrypts and decrypts text using a shuffled character substitution method.

How it works:

Creates a character set (letters, numbers, punctuation + space)
Generates a random shuffled "key" mapping

-    Encryption: swaps each character with its key counterpart
-    Decryption: reverses the process using the same key

Features:

Interactive input for both encrypt/decrypt
One-to-one character substitution (same length input/output)
Random key generation on each run


-->   NOTE: This is for educational purposes only—simple substitution ciphers are easily broken and not secure for real use.

